decks.notes: The deck focuses on quickly filling up the graveyard with high-impact creatures using cards like Entomb and Thoughtseize, then using Reanimate and Animate Dead to bring them back into play for massive value. It also includes disruption cards like Force of Will and Daze to protect the combo and control the opponent's plays. The key strategy is to efficiently reanimate powerful creatures like Archon of Cruelty and Murktide Regent to overwhelm the opponent and win the game quickly. The deck aims to be proactive, disruptive, and powerful in executing its game plan.

This deck focuses on using powerful graveyard-based cards to quickly bring high-impact creatures onto the battlefield, overwhelming opponents with strong creatures early in the game. The key strategy is to utilize cards like Reanimate, Entomb, and Animate Dead to quickly get powerful creatures into play while also utilizing counterspells like Force of Will to protect your game-winning plays. The goal is to outpace and outvalue your opponent by successfully reanimating threats while disrupting their game plan with countermagic and hand disruption spells like Thoughtseize.

The deck aims to utilize combos involving Nadu, Winged Wisdom, Nomads en-Kor, and Misty Rainforest to create an efficient engine that allows for card advantage and control. Key cards such as Green Sun's Zenith and Swords to Plowshares provide additional utility, while cards like Force of Will and Teferi, Time Raveler offer disruption and protection. The deck also includes ramp in the form of Noble Hierarch and card draw with Ponder and Brainstorm. Overall, the deck focuses on building a strong board presence while maintaining control and tempo throughout the game.

This UR Aggro Legacy deck focuses on quickly overwhelming your opponent with efficient creatures and direct damage spells. By utilizing cards like Dragon's Rage Channeler, Murktide Regent, Lightning Bolt, and Brainstorm, you aim to put pressure on your opponent from the start while disrupting their plans with counters like Daze and Force of Will. With a mix of card draw, land disruption with Wasteland, and tempo plays with Stifle, this deck aims to control the game and secure victory through consistent aggression and strategic decision-making.

The deck focuses on utilizing artifacts and efficient mana sources to power out threats quickly and overwhelm opponents. By leveraging cards like Mishra's Bauble and Mox Opal, the deck can generate card advantage and ramp into larger threats like Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Pinnacle Emissary. Urza's Saga provides additional value by tutoring for key artifacts, while Thoughtcast and Force of Will offer disruption and card draw. The goal is to establish a fast and aggressive board presence while maintaining a mixture of card advantage and interaction.

This deck focuses on utilizing the graveyard as a resource to power out strong creatures and win conditions like Thassa's Oracle. By utilizing cards like Faithless Looting and Golgari Thug to fill the graveyard quickly, the deck can easily dredge through its library and establish a strong board presence. Cards like Bridge from Below and Cabal Therapy also help disrupt opponents' strategies while setting up for powerful combo plays. Overall, this deck aims to quickly overwhelm opponents with its graveyard shenanigans and combo potential.

The deck focuses on generating mana quickly and efficiently using cards like Dark Ritual and Lotus Petal to cast powerful spells like Tendrils of Agony or Burning Wish for a combo finish. It also utilizes cards like Thoughtseize and Veil of Summer to protect its combo pieces from disruption. The inclusion of Wishclaw Talisman and Beseech the Mirror allows for tutoring specific cards when needed. Overall, the deck aims to assemble its pieces quickly and overwhelm the opponent with a storm of spells for a game-winning turn.

This deck focuses on quickly filling the graveyard with powerful creatures through cards like Entomb and Reanimate, then bringing them back onto the battlefield for a strong advantage. It also includes control elements like Force of Will and Thoughtseize to protect the combo pieces and disrupt the opponent's strategy. The combo-reanimator archetype aims to quickly and efficiently bring out high-impact creatures from the graveyard to overwhelm the opponent and secure victory. Additionally, the deck includes a mix of threats and disruption to handle a variety of situations.

The deck focuses on using disruptive spells like Thoughtseize, Daze, and Force of Will to control the opponent's board while quickly deploying threats like Murktide Regent and Orcish Bowmasters to put pressure on the opponent. Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student provides card advantage and Baleful Strix helps to slow down aggressive decks. The deck also utilizes fetch lands and Wasteland to disrupt the opponent's mana base. Overall, the deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while presenting a fast clock to win the game.

This Mono Red Combo deck focuses on generating mana quickly with spells like Seething Song and Rite of Flame, while reducing costs with cards like Ruby Medallion. The goal is to cast high-impact spells like Wish','','');">Burning Wish, Bonus Round, and Will of the Jeskai to create explosive turns that can win the game in a single swing. The deck also utilizes powerful planeswalkers like Ral, Monsoon Mage and spells like Wrenn's Resolve to protect its combo pieces and disrupt opponents. Overall, the deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces and overwhelm the opponent with a flurry of spells.

The deck focuses on efficiently disrupting the opponent's game plan while deploying threats and generating value through blink effects. It utilizes a combination of powerful creatures, removal spells, and disruption tools to control the board and apply pressure. By leveraging cards like Aether Vial and Stoneforge Mystic, the deck can quickly assemble equipment and creatures to overwhelm the opponent. The inclusion of Yorion, Sky Nomad as a companion allows for additional value and flexibility in the long game, ensuring a steady stream of threats and answers.

This deck focuses on filling the graveyard quickly with Entomb and using Reanimate to bring powerful creatures back onto the battlefield early in the game. The combo aspect is enhanced with cards like Archon of Cruelty and Atraxa, Grand Unifier, while also providing control elements with cards like Force of Will and Thoughtseize. The inclusion of creatures like Murktide Regent and Brazen Borrower help provide additional threats and disruption. The mana base is optimized for consistency and efficiency, with a balanced mix of dual lands and fetch lands.

This deck focuses on using efficient cards to apply pressure on the opponent quickly. By using cards like Dragon's Rage Channeler and Murktide Regent alongside cheap spells like Lightning Bolt and Daze, the deck aims to control the board while dealing damage to the opponent. This aggressive strategy is supported by cards like Mishra's Bauble and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student to ensure card advantage and consistency. The deck also includes disruption in the form of cards like Force of Will and Wasteland to keep the opponent off balance and unable to stabilize.

The deck focuses on aggressively playing powerful Eldrazi creatures and disrupting the opponent with cards like Chalice of the Void and Thought-Knot Seer. By using mana acceleration like Ancient Tomb and Grim Monolith, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent quickly with threats like Devourer of Destiny and Glaring Fleshraker. The deck also includes ways to protect its creatures with Cavern of Souls and Wasteland to disrupt the opponent's mana base. Overall, the strategy revolves around playing big threats early and maintaining pressure on the opponent throughout the game.

The deck focuses on quickly putting powerful creatures into play from the graveyard, using cards like Animate Dead, Reanimate, and Entomb. It also includes disruptive spells like Thoughtseize and Daze to protect the combo. Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student helps dig for combo pieces, while cards like Brainstorm and Ponder provide card selection. The deck runs a low land count with dual lands to ensure consistency and includes counterspells like Force of Will to protect the combo. Overall, the deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces and overwhelm the opponent with powerful creatures.

The main concept of this deck is to achieve control by utilizing lands to disrupt the opponent's strategy and win conditions. By using cards like Crop Rotation, Life from the Loam, and Wasteland, the deck aims to deny resources and disrupt the opponent's board state. The deck also includes a combo with Dark Depths and Thespian's Stage to create a powerful 20/20 indestructible creature. Additionally, cards like Boseiju, Who Endures and Malevolent Rumble provide protection and removal options to maintain control of the game.
